items.title: Big tech is paying for Trump’s White House ballroom
items.description: Trump's $250 million White House ballroom will be funded in part by big tech companies like Amazon, Apple, Google, Meta, and Microsoft.

items.title: With an Intel recovery underway, all eyes turn to its foundry business
items.description: Intel added $20 billion to its balance sheet in Q3 but didn't offer many details on the progress of its floundering foundry business.

items.title: Ford isn’t going to make more F-150 Lightnings for a while
items.description: Ford is prioritizing its gas and hybrid F-150 trucks instead.
